 "components": {
  "instruction": "Classify the given text into one of these categories: automatic_top_up, balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer, beneficiary_not_allowed, cancel_transfer, card_payment_fee_charged, card_payment_not_recognised, declined_cash_withdrawal, exchange_rate, exchange_via_app, failed_transfer, get_disposable_virtual_card, get_physical_card, passcode_forgotten, pending_top_up, pending_transfer, receiving_money, reverted_card_payment?, top_up_by_cash_or_cheque, top_up_reverted, topping_up_by_card, transfer_fee_charged, transfer_into_account, transfer_timing, verify_my_identity, verify_source_of_funds.\n\nIMPORTANT NOTES:\n1. The category name must be copied EXACTLY as listed above, including any punctuation marks. For example, \"reverted_card_payment?\" includes a question mark at the end - you must include it.\n\n2. Key category distinctions:\n   - \"reverted_card_payment?\" is for when a previous card payment has been reversed/returned to the customer's account\n   - \"balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer\" is for when customers want to check or see their transfers, or when a transfer they made hasn't appeared in their balance\n   - \"get_physical_card\" is for issues related to receiving a physical card or PIN (e.g., waiting for PIN delivery, card hasn't arrived)\n   - \"passcode_forgotten\" is specifically for when a customer has forgotten their passcode/PIN, not for issues with receiving a new one\n\n3. Pay close attention to the context:\n   - Questions about seeing/viewing past transfers → \"balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer\"\n   - Issues with PIN/card delivery or waiting for physical card → \"get_physical_card\"\n   - Payments that have been reversed or come back into account → \"reverted_card_payment?\"\n\nReturn only the category name as your response, with exact spelling and punctuation."
 },
